1294  struct OptionFlags : Bitfield<OptionFlags>
1295  {
1296  enum _enumType : uint16_t
1297  {
1298  NONE = 0x0000,
1299  L1SAIF = 0x0001,
1300  ALL = 0x0001,
1301  };
1302  uint16_t value = NONE;
1303 
1304  OptionFlags() : value(NONE) {}
1305  OptionFlags(int val) : value((uint16_t)val) {}
1306  operator uint16_t() const { return value; }
1307  OptionFlags& operator=(uint16_t val) { value = val; return *this; }
1308  OptionFlags& operator=(int val) { value = val; return *this; }
1309  OptionFlags& operator|=(uint16_t val) { return *this = value | val; }
1310  OptionFlags& operator&=(uint16_t val) { return *this = value & val; }
1311 
1312  bool l1saif() const { return (value & L1SAIF) > 0; }
1313  void l1saif(bool val) { if(val) value |= L1SAIF; else value &= ~L1SAIF; }
1314 
1315  bool allSet() const { return value == ALL; }
1316  void setAll() { value |= ALL; }
1317  };

1417  ALL = 0x0007,
1418  };
1419  uint16_t value = NONE;
1420 
1421  SBASOptions() : value(NONE) {}
1422  SBASOptions(int val) : value((uint16_t)val) {}
1423  operator uint16_t() const { return value; }
1424  SBASOptions& operator=(uint16_t val) { value = val; return *this; }
1425  SBASOptions& operator=(int val) { value = val; return *this; }
1426  SBASOptions& operator|=(uint16_t val) { return *this = value | val; }
1427  SBASOptions& operator&=(uint16_t val) { return *this = value & val; }

1899  struct PinMode : Bitfield<PinMode>
1900  {
1901  enum _enumType : uint8_t
1902  {
1903  NONE = 0x00,
1904  OPEN_DRAIN = 0x01,
1905  PULLDOWN = 0x02,
1906  PULLUP = 0x04,
1907  ALL = 0x07,
1908  };
1909  uint8_t value = NONE;
1910 
1911  PinMode() : value(NONE) {}
1912  PinMode(int val) : value((uint8_t)val) {}
1913  operator uint8_t() const { return value; }
1914  PinMode& operator=(uint8_t val) { value = val; return *this; }
1915  PinMode& operator=(int val) { value = val; return *this; }
1916  PinMode& operator|=(uint8_t val) { return *this = value | val; }
1917  PinMode& operator&=(uint8_t val) { return *this = value & val; }
1918 
1919  bool openDrain() const { return (value & OPEN_DRAIN) > 0; }
1920  void openDrain(bool val) { if(val) value |= OPEN_DRAIN; else value &= ~OPEN_DRAIN; }
1921  bool pulldown() const { return (value & PULLDOWN) > 0; }
1922  void pulldown(bool val) { if(val) value |= PULLDOWN; else value &= ~PULLDOWN; }
1923  bool pullup() const { return (value & PULLUP) > 0; }
1924  void pullup(bool val) { if(val) value |= PULLUP; else value &= ~PULLUP; }
1925 
1926  bool allSet() const { return value == ALL; }
1927  void setAll() { value |= ALL; }
1928  };
1929

2345 struct GetEventTriggerStatus
2346 {
2347  struct Status : Bitfield<Status>
2348  {
2349  enum _enumType : uint8_t
2350  {
2351  NONE = 0x00,
2352  ACTIVE = 0x01,
2353  ENABLED = 0x02,
2354  TEST = 0x04,
2355  ALL = 0x07,
2356  };
2357  uint8_t value = NONE;
2358 
2359  Status() : value(NONE) {}
2360  Status(int val) : value((uint8_t)val) {}
2361  operator uint8_t() const { return value; }
2362  Status& operator=(uint8_t val) { value = val; return *this; }
2363  Status& operator=(int val) { value = val; return *this; }
2364  Status& operator|=(uint8_t val) { return *this = value | val; }
2365  Status& operator&=(uint8_t val) { return *this = value & val; }
2366 
2367  bool active() const { return (value & ACTIVE) > 0; }
2368  void active(bool val) { if(val) value |= ACTIVE; else value &= ~ACTIVE; }
2369  bool enabled() const { return (value & ENABLED) > 0; }
2370  void enabled(bool val) { if(val) value |= ENABLED; else value &= ~ENABLED; }
2371  bool test() const { return (value & TEST) > 0; }
2372  void test(bool val) { if(val) value |= TEST; else value &= ~TEST; }
2373 
2374  bool allSet() const { return value == ALL; }
2375  void setAll() { value |= ALL; }
2376  };

@ ALL
Only allowed for SAVE, LOAD, and DEFAULT function selectors.

@ ACCEL
Accelerometer. Range is specified in g.

@ PRESS

@ MAG

@ GYRO
Gyroscope. Range is specified in degrees/s.
